(21, 1, 10, 'What happens if the computer is not turned off for a windows computer for a long time?', '<p>There are a number of reasons why many people want to keep their computers running. First is convenience. No need to wait for your computer to boot up and applications to load up every time you need to use it. Second is remote access, you can access your computer from anywhere in the world to retrieve data, upload or download large files, or even start a processing process. work management.</p><p>So, have you ever wondered what will happen if you don\'t turn off your Windows computer and use it continuously for a long time? To answer this question, one user decided to experiment and share his interesting findings.</p><h2 style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(41, 41, 41);font-family:Merriweather;font-size:20px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;letter-spacing:normal;margin:0.5em 0px;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-rendering:geometricprecision;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><strong style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;box-sizing:border-box;text-rendering:geometricprecision;\">Windows still has stability when operating for a long time</strong></h2><h2 style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(41, 41, 41);font-family:Merriweather;font-size:20px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;letter-spacing:normal;margin:0.5em 0px;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-rendering:geometricprecision;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacin